description.narrative: Caregivers have improved knowledge and skills to adopt recommended health and nutrition care practices, particularly in target countries., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Immunization, Immunization (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, children in the Pacific, particularly the most vulnerable, increasingly benefit from quality and resilient health and nutrition services and care practices.

description.narrative: ‘Foods for the First 1,000 Days, a cooking-based reality television program featuring local Pacific foods, aired in 12 PICTs and included a UNICEF-sponsored public service announcement (PSA) on the impact and prevention of stunting. Low rates of dietary diversity were addressed through the production of recipes for complementary feeding using locally available foods and a multimedia awareness campaign on stunting, reaching 5,000 villages in Solomon Islands. A regional measles awareness package, including risk communication, reached more than 1 million people across the Pacific in support of the measles outbreak response and SIAs. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
